Investment income for the year ended December 31, 2021 increased versus the year ended December 31, 2020 due to strong
performance of assets underlying our limited partnership investments reported in Other long-term investments. The overall increase
in investment income was partially offset by lower investment income from our debt securities as a result of lower invested asset
levels following the divestiture of Cigna's U.S. Group Disability and Life business on December 31, 2020. The Company received
income distributions of $568 million in 2021, $227 million in 2020 and $202 million in 2019 from its limited partnership
investments reported in Other long-term investments.
D. Realized Investment Gains and Losses
Accounting policy. Realized investment gains and losses are based on specifically identified assets and result from sales, investment
asset write-downs, change in the fair value of certain derivatives and equity securities and changes in allowances for credit losses on
debt securities and commercial mortgage loan investments.
The following realized gains and losses on investments exclude amounts required to adjust future policy benefits for the run-off
settlement annuity business (consistent with accounting for a premium deficiency), as well as realized gains and losses attributed to
the Company's separate accounts because those gains and losses generally accrue directly to separate account policyholders:
