Note 3 — Intercompany receivables of the Company consist primarily of net amounts due from Express Scripts Holdings of
$7.8 billion as of December 31, 2021 and $1.4 billion (consisting of an $8.2 billion receivable offset by a $6.8 billion payable) as of
December 31, 2020. Interest income on the receivable was accrued at an annual fixed rate of 5.50%. Interest expense on the payable
was accrued at an average rate of 0.20% in 2021.
Note 4 — The Company had guarantees of approximately $86 million as of December 31, 2021. These guarantees are primarily
related to outstanding letters of credit. In 2021, no payments have been made on these guarantees.
